From 3f2070d551d3defeb8a87e0e867f44580f379460 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: SlayZone Dev <dev@slayzone.local>
Date: Sun, 19 Apr 2026 02:33:51 +0200
Subject: slayzone: Phase 6.1 tabs.mojom + SlayzoneTabsHost
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Mojom contract in chrome/browser/slayzone/mojom/tabs.mojom mirrors the
shared outer file at packages/shared/mojo-bindings/mojom/tabs.mojom (same
coordinated-exception pattern as 5.6's layout.mojom — Phase 4.3 generates
TS bindings from the outer copy; this in-tree copy is what Chromium's
mojom() target compiles to C++; the two must stay diff-identical).

SlayzoneTabsHost, owned per SlayzoneBrowserView, observes the Browser's
TabStripModel + per-tab title/URL/load changes and fans out full
TabSnapshot lists to every subscribed TabObserver remote. Stable tab
identity uses tabs::TabHandle::raw_value() (survives WebContents
discard/swap). Navigation methods (Load/Back/Fwd/Reload/Stop) act on the
active WebContents; Create uses chrome::AddAndReturnTabAt; Close uses
TabInterface::Close(). Cross-window handles are rejected.

No JS consumer yet — binder registration for the chrome://slayzone-tabbar
and chrome://slayzone-browserchrome hosts lands in Phase 6.3 alongside
the dev JS clients. 6.1 is build-only additive.
